The paper discusses a psychophysical experiment using eye-tracking to study the role of scene layout and regional cues in guiding visual attention. This work is related to computer vision and human-computer interaction, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.CV and cs.HC, respectively. Additionally, the paper proposes a computational model to improve the performance of bottom-up models for fixation prediction, which falls under the sub-categories cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
